cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.CR 

This paper describes the system architecture of a commercial RDBMS system, which makes appropriate architectural choices to achieve high performance expected from modern "web scale" analytic systems. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the following sub-categories: 
- cs.DB (Database)
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms)
- cs.SE (Software Engineering)
- cs.PL (Programming Languages)
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security)
